gomodel:SYNGO_70  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: It is demonstrated that a PKC alpha knockout has a reduction in post-tetanic potentiation (PTP), in the Calyx of Held. It is also shown that PTP operates at least partly due to a potentiation in readily releasable pool size, and that this potentiation is diminished in the PKC alpha/beta knockout.\n\nIt should be noted that in some synapses, PKC alpha is not required for PTP (Wang et.al. 2016).. Experimental description: Robust PTP was observed in wild-type mice. (...) Representative experiments show that somewhat smaller PTP was observed in PKCα-/- animals (Figure 2B), and PTP was greatly reduced in PKCβ-/- (Figure 2C) and PKCα-/-β-/- mice (Figure 2D)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_70" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

